kids-shoes.name: Tatum 2
kids-shoes.description: Pulled out of the vault, these low tops are back. Inspired by the original Wings logo and design of the AJ1, these all-day, everyday shoes are ready for whatever. Smooth leather uppers and a big embossed logo will help you stand out, however you style 'em.

kids-shoes.name: Jordan Nu Retro 1 Low
kids-shoes.description: An iconic look that lasts. This AJ1 pairs the classic design of the original with premium materials that will keep you going all day.

kids-shoes.name: Nike Blazer Low '77
kids-shoes.description: This iteration of the AJ1 re-imagines Mike's first signature model with a fresh mix of colours. Premium materials, soft cushioning and a padded ankle collar offer total support and celebrate the shoe that started it all.

kids-shoes.name: Air Jordan 1 Low
kids-shoes.description: Zion's third signature shoe celebrates the dedication he puts in to crafting his singular game. Packed with court-ready tech, it's designed for ballers who are masters of both land and air. Stay low and contained, then explode skywards, with a cushioned return to earth. The Zion 3 helps hold you down—so you can fly your own way.

kids-shoes.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid
kids-shoes.description: Pulled out of the vault, these low tops are back. Inspired by the original Wings logo and design of the AJ1, these all-day, everyday shoes are ready for whatever. Smooth leather uppers and a big embossed logo will help you stand out, however you style 'em.

kids-shoes.name: Zion 3
kids-shoes.description: Zion's third signature shoe celebrates the dedication he puts in to crafting his singular game. Packed with court-ready tech, it's designed for ballers who are masters of both land and air. Stay low and contained, then explode skywards, with a cushioned return to earth. The Zion 3 helps hold you down—so you can fly your own way.

kids-shoes.name: Nike Air Max Plus
kids-shoes.description: Who says kids don't deserve big cushioning? Not us. Get a taste of our legendary Tuned Air technology with the Nike Air Max Plus. From the school playground to your back garden, these comfy kicks are ready to play with breathable mesh fabric up top and a durable rubber sole underfoot. Plus, wavy design lines and iconic plastic accents celebrate bold style.

kids-shoes.name: Nike Blazer Mid '77
kids-shoes.description: Powered by flowers, these sneakers are all about stopping to appreciate the little things. A legend on the basketball court when first released in the '70s, the Nike Blazer Mid '77 is now an icon off the court with its mid-top collar and durable design. Throwback style with modern materials means you can run, skip and jump in comfort.

kids-shoes.name: Nike Dynamo 2 EasyOn
kids-shoes.description: Meet the shoes designed to keep up with your little one. Easy, snug and built for play at any time, the Nike Dynamo 2 EasyOn is all about helping kids get going fast. They can stomp down on the collapsible heel and slip their feet in. Or, if they're not quite ready to do it themselves, you can show them how it works by pushing down on the heel. Worm-like lines across the stretchy fabric upper wrap little feet in flexible comfort and support.

kids-shoes.name: Nike Flex Advance
kids-shoes.description: Pulled out of the vault, these low tops are back. Inspired by the original Wings logo and design of the AJ1, these all-day, everyday shoes are ready for whatever. Smooth leather uppers and a big embossed logo will help you stand out, however you style 'em.
kids-shoes.colors: Pink Glaze/Violet Ore/Light Violet Ore/Pink Glaze

kids-shoes.name: Nike Air Force 1 LV8 2
kids-shoes.description: Make a splash in shoes as fun as you. As cool today as when it first dropped more than 40 years ago, the AF-1 is a classic you can count on. Its durable construction, Air cushioning and grippy tread will see you through break time after break time. Pops of bright colours and reflective design Swoosh logos add eye-catching style. And while these sneakers look great fresh out of the box, they remain cool when covered in scuffs and scrapes. In fact, they might be even better.

kids-shoes.name: Nike Star Runner 4 NN SE
kids-shoes.description: Made for running to catch the ice-cream van, games of tag and races to the end of the street and back, this special-edition Nike Star Runner 4 lets you blast off into fun. Soft cushioning in the midsole helps provide a comfortable, springy return so every skip, hop and stride you take puts you one step closer to the finishing line. Plus, the tread grabs at pavement, grass and gravel to help give you extra grip. A rubber-wrapped toe box toughens up the construction so you can go further in the same pair of sneakers.

kids-shoes.name: Nike Sunray Protect 2
kids-shoes.description: The Nike Sunray Protect 2 Sandals deliver total toe coverage and outsole traction that's perfect for outdoor play. Hook-and-loop straps make on and off easy, while openings on the top of the shoe promote airflow when little feet get hot.

kids-shoes.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid SE
kids-shoes.description: Take note: the adults in your life might have rules, but they can also inspire some amazing drip. Inspired by the wallpaper in MJ's childhood home, this AJ1 rocks bold florals and colour-blocked canvas.

kids-shoes.name: Nike Jr. Phantom Luna 2 Academy
kids-shoes.description: You've found the net, whether you set up a pal with a great pass or made a fantastic move. Now, go and score. This boot has a sticky texture where you kick the ball the hardest. That way, you have control of your shot when the net is in range. We created it with goals in mind.

kids-shoes.name: Nike Air Max 90 LTR
kids-shoes.description: The Nike Air Max 90 takes the original look to a new level with more comfort and flexibility, while keeping the classic Max Air cushioning you know and love.

kids-shoes.name: LeBron XXI SE 'Movie Night'
kids-shoes.description: Where will your game take you? Lace up the latest from the King and find out. With Air Zoom units and soft cushioning, the LeBron XXI (also known as the LeBron 21) offers you flexibility and power without slowing you down with excess weight. Ideal for rim runs, fast breaks and racing up and down the court, they'll help you keep playing at the top of your game until the final buzzer sounds.

kids-shoes.name: JA 1
kids-shoes.description: Ja Morant became the superstar he is today by practising his game wherever possible. That same drive for greatness led to Ja seeing a childhood dream come true when he signed with Nike. On top of getting a signature shoe, he received a Nike employee badge, which is like an all-access pass to our World Headquarters. Full of lightweight and springy cushioning, this shoe celebrates Ja's love of the Swoosh and his rise from long-time brand admirer to signature ambassador.

kids-shoes.name: Nike E-Series 1.0
kids-shoes.description: Shoes made for almost any occasion. Playtime? Sure. School? Yes. Activities with friends? Of course! The Nike E-Series 1.0 is the everyday shoe. The highlight is a lace-free design that stretches wide (helped by a hidden strap) so it's easy to slip feet in. Combining plush comfort underfoot and stability where it's needed, we have 1 goal: making sure you're confident and have fun every time you pull on your kicks.

kids-shoes.name: Nike Team Hustle D 11
kids-shoes.description: From first steps to future first baskets, cover all of playtime with the Nike Team Hustle D 11. Our top priority with this edition of the Team Hustle D series was making them easy to get on. Big straps let you open the shoes up wide so little feet can slip in and get going. Plus, cushioning is more plush than previous editions, helping make each step more comfortable. The ultimate play shoe just got better.
kids-shoes.colors: Summit White/Coconut Milk/Light Photo Blue/Barely Volt

jordan-shoes.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid SE
jordan-shoes.description: You never know where self-belief might take you. Inspired by the texture and colours of a passport, and the stamps MJ collected on his world tours, this AJ1 is a fresh reminder to dream big. Keep the included luggage tag as an adornment for your shoes (or your suitcase).
jordan-shoes.colors: Colour Shown: Armoury Navy/Pale Ivory/Sport Red/Metallic Gold

jordan-shoes.name: Tatum 2 PF
jordan-shoes.description: It's not over until you hear that buzzer. Fly through your game with energy to spare in the Tatum 2. It helps you stay light on your feet by limiting the use of heavy rubber. A full-length Nike Air Strobel unit helps support your quick shifts, and the frame pairs with supportive foam that moulds to your feet for a contained feel.

jordan-shoes.name: Jordan Spizike Low
jordan-shoes.description: Drawing from the iconic colourway of the 2006 AJ4 release, this Varsity Maize edition of the Spizike Low brings a radiant burst of colour to the hoops-infused classic. It combines signature elements from past Jordan models such as Varsity Maize leather, elephant print trim and a translucent outsole. The result is a mash-up of layers, textures and nostalgia. To finish off your look, a Jumpman logo and branded lace locks seal the deal.

jordan-shoes.name: Jumpman MVP
jordan-shoes.description: We didn't invent the remix—but considering the material we get to sample, this one's a no-brainer. We took elements from the AJ6, 7 and 8, making them into a completely new shoe that celebrates MJ's first 3-peat championship run. With leather, textile and nubuck details, these sneakers honour one legacy while encouraging you to cement your own.

jordan-shoes.name: Zion 3 'Rising' PF
jordan-shoes.description: Every challenge Zion faces—intense training, the team at the other end of the court or even gravity itself—you know he's going to rise above. This version of the Zion 3, with it's dreamy gradient fade, channels the energy that comes with every new day. And the performance tech gives you the assist you need when getting low and going high.

jordan-shoes.name: Air Jordan Legacy 312 Low
jordan-shoes.description: Who doesn't love a good mash-up? Taking elements from the AJ1, AJ3 and the Nike Air Alpha Force, these kicks encompass the best of the best. Iconic details (check out that elephant print and midfoot strap) honour MJ's time in Chicago's 312 area code. With premium materials and Nike Air cushioning, this is the beginning of a whole new legacy.

jordan-shoes.name: Air Jordan 1 Low SE Craft
jordan-shoes.description: Each Craft released puts a handmade feel on the AJ1 and these low-cut sneakers are no exception. Sandy neutrals come together in kicks that beg to be a part of every outfit. Premium suede adds texture while a lightly speckled outsole grounds your look with subtle detail.

jordan-shoes.name: Air Jordan XXXVIII Low PF
jordan-shoes.description: Get grounded, stay grounded. The AJ XXXVIII is all about groundwork—we're talking about your running, your cutting, your turn-around jumpers—with low-to-the-court cushioning and a secure upper that helps support every move. It's also designed with sustainability in mind, with at least 20% recycled content by weight. So you can hit 'em with that windscreen-wiper fake and feel good about more than just sinking a bucket for your team.

jordan-shoes.name: Air Jordan 9 G
jordan-shoes.description: MJ's baseball tenure brought an incomparable buzz to the sport world. Every swing, shag and stolen base was scrutinised. In addition to the baseball pitches of Birmingham, he created fascinating moments on the courts of Chicago and numerous golf courses around the world. This special AJ9 threads together all three sports and celebrates MJ's minor-league stint with pinstriped insoles, classic club colours and, of course, the iconic #45 decal on the heel.

jordan-shoes.name: Jordan 1 Mid SE
jordan-shoes.description: Welcome to MJ's playground! Inspired by painted outdoor basketball courts, these multi-coloured Js add a distinctive pop to your little one's 'fit. Mesh on the tongue adds nothing-but-net style while premium suede, smooth leather and a mid-top silhouette add a heritage Jordan look everyone on the playground will want.

jordan-shoes.name: Jordan One Take 5
jordan-shoes.description: Accelerate, bank, shoot, score—then repeat. Russell Westbrook's latest shoe is here to assist your speed game so you can stay unstoppable on the break. The lateral eyestay and wraparound toe piece help you feel contained on the court. Underfoot, you get energy-returning Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot so you can keep sinkin' 'em from the first to the fourth.

jordan-shoes.name: Zion 3 'Orchid' SE PF
jordan-shoes.description: Sophistication on foot, domination on the court: this Zion 3 is M.U.D. (Made Uniquely Different). The nubuck leather and suede give you a luxe look. The special-edition forefoot strap lets you customise your containment, while full-length Zoom Air further sets this pair apart. The tonal mud-splatter embroidery adds grit to the super-clean light purple upper—a reminder of what it takes to achieve greatness.

jordan-shoes.name: Jumpman MVP
jordan-shoes.description: We didn't invent the remix—but considering the material we get to sample, this one's a no-brainer. We took elements from the AJ6, 7 and 8, making them into a completely new shoe that celebrates MJ's first 3-peat championship run. With leather, textile and nubuck details, these sneakers honour one legacy while encouraging you to cement your own.

jordan-shoes.name: Air Jordan 4 Retro
jordan-shoes.description: The AJ4 delivers responsive cushioning, with a heel Air-Sole unit bringing the street-ready comfort. Leather on the upper offers a premium look and heritage style. Whether you're wearing 'em at dusk or dawn, this design from '89 is the perfect off-court flex.

jordan-shoes.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro
jordan-shoes.description: Get your piece of Jordan history and heritage with the Air Jordan 5 Retro.Based on the classic game shoe from 1990, it has all the iconic details, including the bump-out collar, lace toggle and fighter plane-inspired design lines.

jordan-shoes.name: Zion 3 PF
jordan-shoes.description: Zion's third signature shoe celebrates the dedication he puts in to crafting his singular game. Packed with court-ready tech, it's designed for ballers who are masters of both land and air. Stay low and contained, then explode skywards, with a cushioned return to earth. The Zion 3 helps hold you down—so you can fly your own way.            .

jordan-shoes.name: Jumpman MVP
jordan-shoes.description: Honour Jordan's first 3 championships with a pair of kicks that collects details from each respective year's shoe and collages them together into one fire homage. Elements of the AJ6, 7 and 8 come to life in fresh new ways, right on your feet.

jordan-shoes.name: Air Jordan XXXVIII

The AJ XXXVIII is all about groundwork—we're talking about your running, your cutting, your turn-around jumpers—with low-to-the-court cushioning and a secure upper that helps support every move. It's also designed with sustainability in mind, with at least 20% recycled content by weight. So you can hit 'em with that windscreen-wiper fake and feel good about more than just sinking a bucket for your team.

jordan-shoes.name: Tatum 1 'Denim' PF
jordan-shoes.description: Jayson Tatum is known for his off-court looks as much as his on-court moves (well, almost). In this special-edition Tatum 1, you can stunt on 'em like a tunnel-walk champion. Denim-inspired, but still ready to ball. Who says you can't play in jeans?

jordan-shoes.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Craft
jordan-shoes.description: Dark, stormy and full of style. This AJ1 combines leather, suede and textiles in the upper for a tonal look with plenty of depth.
